cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with information extraction from medical text, specifically drug name recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes new data representation techniques based on word embeddings and deep learning models, which suggests a connection to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the challenges of dealing with unstructured text and lack of labeled datasets, which suggests a connection to categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
